Title: Two Simple Residual Bounds for the Eigenvalues of Hermitian Matrices  
Author: G. W. Stewart 
Address: College Park, MD  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science and Institute for Advanced Computer Studies, University of Maryland,  
Date: 89-123 December 1989 CS-TR 2364  
Note: UMIACS-TR  20742. This work was supported in part by the Air Force Office of Sponsored Research under Contract AFOSR-87-0188.  
Abstract: Let A be Hermitian and let the orthonormal columns of X span an approximate invariant subspace of X. Then the residual R = AX XM (M = X H AX) will be small. The theorems of this paper bound the distance of the spectrum of M from the spectrum of A in terms of appropriate norms of R. 
